data.body:
I'm posting here because it's not specific to one theme, but all.

Examples:
https://github.com/atom/solarized-dark-syntax
https://github.com/atom/base16-tomorrow-light-theme

If you check `index.less`, appears this:

```less
@import "colors";
@import "syntax-variables";

// Editor
@import "editor";

// Languages
@import "syntax/_base";
@import "syntax/c";
// ...
```

But that directory structure doesn't exist! Everything is inside  `styles` folder.

So.. how does the less files resolves correctly?

I also noticed that doing `apm install <theme>`, installs the package with the same contents (so apparently broken and unresolvable)
